Competition: Copa Ibarguren


* Argentina - Copa Ibarguren

* Overview

*  The Minister of Public Instruction, Dr Carlos Ibarguren, donated this cup to be played by the champions of the all regional leagues. But, it was only played by champions of:
* 1913-1938: National league vs. Rosario league.
* 1939:      National league vs. Litoral tournament (Paraná, Rosario and 
*            Santa Fe).
* 1940-1941: National league vs. Rosario league.
* 1942-1958: National league vs. "Copa Presidente".

* Palmares

* 1913  Racing Club (Avellaneda)
* 1914  Racing Club (Avellaneda)
* 1915  Rosario Central (Rosario)
* 1916  Racing Club (Avellaneda)
* 1917  Racing Club (Avellaneda)
* 1918  Racing Club (Avellaneda)
* 1919  Boca Juniors (Buenos Aires)
* 1920  Tiro Federal (Rosario)
* 1921  Newell's Old Boys (Rosario)
* 1922  Huracán (Buenos Aires)
* 1923  Boca Juniors (Buenos Aires)
* 1924  Boca Juniors (Buenos Aires)
* 1925  Huracán (Buenos Aires)
* 1937  River Plate (Buenos Aires)
* 1938  Independiente (Avellaneda)
* 1939  Independiente (Avellaneda)
* 1940  Boca Juniors (Buenos Aires)
* 1941  River Plate (Buenos Aires)
* 1942  River Plate (Buenos Aires)
* 1944  Boca Juniors (Buenos Aires)
* 1950  Liga Mendocina (Mendoza)
* 1952   abandoned
* 1958  Liga Cordobesa (Córdoba)? 

